This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with adaptive learning rate methods for training deep neural networks. It may also belong to cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) as it proposes a novel preconditioner for optimization problems. Additionally, it could be relevant to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is commonly used in these fields. Finally, it could also be relevant to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as it deals with optimization algorithms.
